  "title": "Testing, Static Quality, Performance, and Release",
  "description": "Harden the service-data client with behavioral tests, deterministic fixtures, performance evidence, and a clean release. Learners cumulatively produce a tested and release-ready JavaScript application through theory, guided work, debugging, transfer, retrieval, and assessment.",
  "order": 14,
  "objectives": [
    "Design tests around observable behavior, changed inputs, boundaries, and failures rather than implementation lines.",
    "Use fakes, stubs, spies, and controlled clocks only at owned boundaries without mocking away the behavior under test.",
    "Await asynchronous outcomes, control timers and network fixtures, and fail on unhandled work deterministically."
